For the wavelet type orthonormal systems $\phi_n$, we establish a new bound
			\begin{equation}
			\left\|\max_{1\le m\le n}\left|\sum_{j\in G_m}\langle f,\phi_j\rangle \phi_j\right|\right\|_p\lesssim \sqrt{\log (n+1)}\cdot \|f\|_p,\quad 1<p<\infty,
		\end{equation}
	where $G_m\subset {\mathbb N}$ are arbitrary sets of indexes.	Using this estimate, we prove that $\log n$ is an almost everywhere convergence Weyl multiplier for any orthonormal system of non-overlapping wavelet polynomials. It will also be remarked that  $\log n$ is the optimal sequence in this context.
